  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Heavy rainfall in the state of MG has caused flooding in some cities, Rio Casca, Vista Alegre and Aguas Ferreas. According to data from the civil defense, around 2200 people are displaced in Rio Casca, 1000 in the Vista Alegre and 1000 in the district of Aguas Ferreas. Rio rose about 10 meters. Houses, schools, public buildingsfarms and pastures were totally destroyed by the force of the waters. Around 2000 people are housed in hospitals and schools that were not affected by the floods. The cities are covered with mud that mixes with the sewage, bringing a very unpleasant bad smell. Most of the population lost their homes and everything that inside it, the water level reached the ceiling.</narrative>
  </description>
